doki.background.path.description: Absolute file path of the image you want to use as your empty editor background.

doki.background.enabled.description: Whether you want an image in your empty editor background when running the 'Install Wallpaper' command.

doki.background.anchor.description: Value to be used for css 'background-position' for both images (eg: center, right, left, etc.)

doki.wallpaper.path.description: Absolute file path of the image you want to use as your glass pane wallpaper. (Image should be transparent)

doki.wallpaper.enabled.description: Whether you want an image on top of your code editor, when running the 'Install Wallpaper' command.

doki.statusbar.name.description: Custom name you can use that shows up in the status bar next to the ❤️

doki.sticker.path.description: Absolute file path of the image you want to use as your sticker.

doki.sticker.css.description: Additional CSS stylings you can apply to the installed sticker (such as positioning).
